The evidence with the title 'Overworked America: 12 charts that will make your blood boil ... ' says Productivity has surged, but income and wages have stagnated for most  ... Increase in real value of the minimum wage since 1990 : 21 %  ... For Americans as awhole , the length of a typical workweek has n't changed much in years . But for many middle - class workers , job obligations are creeping into free time and family time.
